{"questionId":"4880","questionHtml":"<p>The structural formula of urea is shown.</p>\n<p><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4469/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-07_om_11.43.42.png\" alt=\"M18/4/CHEMI/HP2/ENG/TZ1/01.b_01\"></p>\n<p>Predict the electron domain and molecular geometries at the nitrogen and carbon atoms, applying the VSEPR theory.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4470/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-07_om_11.45.16.png\" alt=\"M18/4/CHEMI/HP2/ENG/TZ1/01.b_02\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4471/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-07_om_11.46.41.png\" alt=\"M18/4/CHEMI/HP2/ENG/TZ1/01.b/M\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Note: Urea’s structure is more complex&nbsp;</em><em>than that predicted from VSEPR theory.</em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"4880","referenceCode":"18M.2.hl.TZ1.1b","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"The structural formula of urea is shown. Predict the electron domain and molecular geometries at the nitrogen and carbon atoms, applying the VSEPR theory.","paper":"2","level":"hl","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Chemical bonding and structure","4.3 Covalent structures","Core","Topic 4: Chemical bonding and structure"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}